Since the ZnO film with tZnO = 1200 nm exhibited maximum photosensitivity, the incident photon-to-electron conversion efficiency (IPCE) factor of the film was also evaluated for photovoltaic device applications. IPCE is the ratio of the number of photogenerated charge carriers under short-circuit conditions to the number of incident photons at a particular wavelength and is a crucial parameter in the fabrication of photovoltaic devices. The IPCE efficiency is calculated using the following relation [35, 36].4IPCE =jphmAcm2×1239.8V×nmPmonomWcm2×λnm×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
